{"vulnerableLines": "3-25", "vulnerableCode": ["for (j = 0; j < addresses.length; j++) {", "    balanceOf[addresses[j]] = balanceOf[addresses[j]].add(amounts[j]);", "    emit Transfer(msg.sender, addresses[j], amounts[j]);", "    transferIns[addresses[j]].push(transferInStruct(uint256(amounts[j]),_now));"], "vulnerabilityReason": "The airdrop function transfers funds to multiple addresses without checking whether each transfer is successful. If any address is malicious and executes a call during the transfer, it could repeatedly call this function and drain the contractâ€™s funds.", "potentialSecurityRisk": "Malicious recipients could repeatedly receive funds from the airdrop operation, as thereâ€™s no sanity check on the integrity of the transfers after they are initiated.", "fixedCode": "for (j = 0; j < addresses.length; j++) {
    require(amounts[j] > 0 && addresses[j]!= address(0));
    balanceOf[addresses[j]] = balanceOf[addresses[j]].add(amounts[j]);
